feat(gui): implement JavaFX GUI for Nebula chatbot
commitResults.messageBody:
- Add JavaFX entry point (GuiMain/Launcher) with dual-mode support
- Implement MainWindow controller with Nebula backend integration
- Create DialogBox component for user/bot message rendering
- Enhance Ui class with getXXXMessage() methods for GUI string responses
- Add Nebula.getResponse() to return formatted strings (CLI/GUI compatible)
- Configure Gradle with JavaFX dependencies and cross-platform support
- Fix FXML controller references to use fully qualified class names
- Organize resources in src/main/resources (view/, images/)

GUI launched via ./gradlew run displays interactive chat interface
with full task management functionality (todo/deadline/event/mark/delete).
CLI mode remains fully functional via nebula.Nebula.main().

docs: add assertions to document critical invariants
commitResults.messageBody:
- Add pre/postcondition assertions in TaskList (add/delete/mark/unmark)
- Document domain invariants in Deadline/Event constructors and toString()
- Verify state changes in Nebula command handlers (mark/delete/add)
- All assertions target internal logic errors (not user input validation)

commitResults.messageTitle: refactor: improve code quality in Storage and Nebula classes
commitResults.messageBody:
- Fix delimiter inconsistency in Storage.java to prevent data corruption
  (use single DELIMITER constant for both parsing and serialization)
- Extract command handlers from Nebula.getResponse() into focused methods
  (handleMark/unmark/delete/todo/deadline/event/find) for maintainability
- Eliminate raw types in TaskList by adding proper generic typing
- Add strategic assertions to document critical invariants
- Preserve CLI/GUI dual-mode functionality with zero behavior changes

commitResults.messageTitle: refactor(TaskList): replace manual loop with Stream API in find()
commitResults.messageBody:
- Convert find() method to use Stream.filter() for cleaner filtering logic
- Maintain identical behavior and O(n) complexity
- Demonstrates modern Java usage while improving readability
Add assertions to document critical invariants
